<br>
Your point that each offensive RA only affects one type of attack is a good one. If 3% more hit points keeps you alive 3% longer, then that's 3% more offense you can use (in theory).<br>
<br>
One complication, though, is that offense is &quot;chunky&quot; and hit points are not. For example, if MoP gets you an extra crit once in a while, the value of that single crit will likely be more damage points than the 3% increase in hit points from toughness. Some fights that crit will make the difference, and others it won't matter.<br>
<br>
The 3% extra hit points, though, seem to only come into play if you are lucky enough to take a hit within that 3% window. If you are being hit for 300 a shot and you get +30 hit points, most of the time you won't live any longer; the same number of shots will still kill you unless the last one (before you die) happens to be just over your former hit points but less than your new total.  Of course, for those times that you live for one more shot, you likely get another attack in return, so maybe it's a moot point.<br>
<br>
Regardless, even if offense = defense, then it seems better to gather up several of the 1-point offense &amp; defense RA's before getting the second level of any of them. That second 3% of hit points costs 1% per realm point, and you can get MoP, Aug Acuity and something else for the same investment.<br>
<br>
Needless to say, it's all very complex; these are just my ponderings of the moment.   :-)   Thanks for your detailed analysis!<br>
<br>
- Moztli<br>
<br>
