Good point. With all this chunkiness, we should petition for a &quot;salsa&quot; RA and be done with it. :-)<br>
<br>
As for &quot;you hit a lot more than you get hit,&quot; I'm struggling with this assertion as well. At first my reaction was &quot;well, I'm always attacking, but only sometimes is someone fighting back.&quot; But then I realized the opposite is also true -- sometimes I am simply being attacked, because I am stunned or rooted, fighting multiple opponents, caught by a stealther, etc.<br>
<br>
Especially when hit points are a &quot;universal&quot; defense and offensive RA's are split (melee/spell), the defensive bonus seems to be at least as good as more offense. After all (as mbolme points out), just as with a few extra hit points, most of the time that extra crit or few points of DD make no difference. Occasionally you will get lucky and get the kill one hit earlier, just as with more hit points you will occasionally live one hit longer.<br>
<br>
I welcome more discussion on the superiority of offense vs. defense, because the closer I look the less obvious it seems. I can certainly see how offense can be more &quot;fun&quot; and visible, in the form of crits and extra damage that you can see as it happens -- but in terms of math, I don't yet see how offense is inherently better.<br>
<br>
