<br>
this is how nearly all rvr encounters begin.  either you sneak up on the bad guys and aoe mez them or they do it to you.<br>
<br>
now say you have one of the rare RvR healers who actually has enough rps for both perfect recovery (which they get before purge) and purge, so the healer purges the mez.  as soon as the healer starts to cast anything, what is going to happen?  all 8 enemies go right for the healer.<br>
<br>
how do you get 8 enemies off your healer?  personally i mez one, snare one, attack one caster, and interrupt another caster with DDs.  or two casters with DDs.  the instant you interrupt them i have never once found a caster who keeps nuking your healer, they always turn to you.<br>
<br>
so i can quite easily get 4 or maybe 5 attackers off the healer.  <br>
<br>
other than a healer, a skald has more ability to turn the tide of an encounter than any other character in the game.  a skald can stop 5.  champions can stop 3, bards can stop 4, minstrels can stop 4, skalds can stop 5.<br>
<br>
or, you can just sit there mezd as your group is hacked to pieces.  pick whichever option you like.<br>
